HEADWORD: Milldam
<hw>Mill"dam`</hw> <pr>(m⟦icr⟧l"d⟦acr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A dam
or mound to obstruct a water course, and raise the water to a height
sufficient to turn a mill wheel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Milled</ent>⟦br⟧
